//web.archive.org/web/20210112090832/https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/08/tech/trump-twitter-ban/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[推特|推特]]对特朗普的推特账号进行了长达12小时的锁定，并删除了他的三条推文，原因是他发帖公开纵容暴力冲击国会的支持者，违反了推特政策，其后更进一步永久锁定了他的推特账号。<ref name="twitter-lock" /><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Karni|first1=Annie|last2=Haberman|first2=Maggie|date=2021-01-06|title=Trump openly condones supporters who violently stormed the Capitol, prompting Twitter to lock his account.|language=en-US|work=紐約時報|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/06/us/politics/trump-protesters.html|access-date=2021-01-07|issn=0362-4331|archivedate=2021-01-07|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107005643/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/06/us/politics/trump-protesters.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Fung|first=Brian|title=Twitter bans President Trump permanently|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/08/tech/trump-twitter-ban/index.html|access-date=2021-01-09|work=CNN|archivedate=2021-01-12|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112090832/https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/08/tech/trump-twitter-ban/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[Facebook|Facebook]]和[[Instagram|Instagram]]亦跟隨推特以煽動暴力為由臨時封鎖特朗普的帳戶<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/recode/22217705/facebook-twitter-youtube-parler-insurrection-trump-capitol|title=Facebook blocks Trump’s accounts indefinitely|work=Vox|date=2021-01-07|accessdate=2021-01-08|language=en-us|archivedate=2021-01-11|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111070244/https://www.vox.com/recode/22217705/facebook-twitter-youtube-parler-insurrection-trump-capitol|dead-url=no}}</ref>，[[YouTube|YouTube]]則隱藏了多條特朗普發布懷疑煽動暴力的影片<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/recode/22217705/facebook-twitter-youtube-parler-insurrection-trump-capitol|title=Facebook and Twitter suspend Trump’s accounts after Capitol insurrection|work=Vox|date=2021-01-06|accessdate=2021-01-07|language=en-us|archivedate=2021-01-11|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111070244/https://www.vox.com/recode/22217705/facebook-twitter-youtube-parler-insurrection-trump-capitol|dead-url=no}}</ref>。骚乱一周之后，美国众议院以特朗普[[煽动叛乱|煽动叛乱]][[第二次特朗普弹劾案|第二次弹劾他]]，使他成为了美国历史上第一位被弹劾两次的总统<ref name=":10">{{Cite news |last=Fandos |first=Nicholas |date=2021-01-13 |title=The House impeaches Trump for 'incitement of insurrection,' setting up a Senate trial |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/13/us/incitement-of-insurrection.html |access-date=2021-01-14 |archive-date=2021-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114144345/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/13/us/incitement-of-insurrection.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。众议院随后通过了一项法案要求仿照[[美国国家恐怖袭击事件委员会|911委员会]]的模式建立一个两党独立委员会来调查冲击事件<ref name="mFGP2">{{cite news|title=Pelosi announces independent 9/11-style commission on deadly Capitol riot|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2021/02/15/bipartisan-support-grows-for-9/11-style-inquiry-into-deadly-capitol-riot.html|work=CNBC|access-date=2021-02-15|archive-date=2021-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215210556/https://www.cnbc.com/2021/02/15/bipartisan-support-grows-for-9/11-style-inquiry-into-deadly-capitol-riot.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但该法案在参议院被共和党人阻击<ref name="AP_BlockCommission">{{cite news | title=GOP blocks Capitol riot probe, displaying loyalty to Trump | first1=Mary Clare | last1=Jalonick | first2=Lisa | last2=Mascaro | url=https://apnews.com/article/michael-pence-donald-trump-capitol-siege-government-and-politics-4798a8617bacf27bbb576a4b805b85d9 | date=2021-05-28 | access-date=2021-06-02 | work=[[美联社|Associated Press]] | archive-date=2021-07-28 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210728204250/https://apnews.com/article/michael-pence-donald-trump-capitol-siege-government-and-politics-4798a8617bacf27bbb576a4b805b85d9 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。佩洛西随后提议，并被众议院所批准，成立众议院[[美國眾議院1月6日襲擊事件特別委員會|特别委员会]]来调查袭击事件<ref name="selectcom">{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/06/30/politics/house-vote-january-6-select-committee/index.html|title=House votes to create select committee to investigate January 6 insurrection|date=2021-06-30|work=CNN|access-date=2021-07-03|archive-date=2021-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210704094447/https://www.cnn.com/2021/06/30/politics/house-vote-january-6-select-committee/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。时任[[联邦调查局|联邦调查局]]局长的[[克里斯托弗·A·雷|克里斯托弗·雷]]将冲击事件列为{{tsl|en|Domestic terrorism in the United States|美国国内恐怖主义|国内恐怖主义}}事件<ref name="vtWrj">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/03/02/us/joe-biden-news|title=Live Updates: F.B.I. Director Warns Senators That Domestic Terrorism Is ‘Metastasizing Across the Country’|first=Adam|last=Goldman|date=2021-03-02|website=NYTimes.com|access-date=2021-03-28|archive-date=2021-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210303053211/https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/03/02/us/joe-biden-news|dead-url=no}}</ref>。舆论调查显示，大多数美国人不赞成冲击国会大厦，也不赞成特朗普在冲击前后的行为，尽管一些[[共和黨_(美國)|共和党人]]支持这次冲击或至少没有指责特朗普<ref>多个来源：
