在投票站关闭仅数小时后，选票仍在统计中，特朗普宣布胜利并要求停止计票<ref>{{cite news |last1=Burns |first=Alexander |last2=Martin |first2=Jonathan |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/04/us/politics/election-trump-biden-recap.html |title=As America Awaits a Winner, Trump Falsely Claims He Prevailed |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |date=November 4, 2021 |access-date=August 9, 2021 |archive-date=2020-11-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201104063229/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/04/us/politics/election-trump-biden-recap.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他开始了一场通过法律挑战和法外努力来颠覆选举的运动<ref name="Rutenberg">{{Cite web|date=February 1, 2021|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/31/us/trump-election-lie.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201000107/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/31/us/trump-election-lie.html|archive-date=2021-02-01|url-access=limited|newspaper=The New York Times|quote=Trump's{{nbs}}... effort to reverse his loss turned into{{nbs}}... an extralegal campaign to subvert the election, rooted in a lie so convincing to some of his most devoted followers that it made the deadly January{{nbs}}6 assault on the Capitol almost inevitable{{nbs}}... With each passing day the lie grew, finally managing to do what the political process and the courts would not: upend the peaceful transfer of power that for 224 years had been the bedrock of American democracy.|title=77 Days: Trump's Campaign to Subvert the Election|last1=Rutenberg|first1=Jim|last2=Becker|first2=Jo|last3=Lipton|first3=Eric|last4=Haberman|first4=Maggie|last5=Martin|first5=Jonathan|last6=Rosenberg|first6=Matthew|last7=Schmidt|first7=Michael S.|access-date=2022-01-09|dead-url=no}}{{cbignore}}</ref>。尽管特朗普的律师在选举后十天内得出结论，对选举结果的法律挑战没有事实依据或法律依据<ref name="Rutenberg"/>，但特朗普仍试图推翻选举结果，提出了至少60起诉讼，其中两起被提交给[[美国最高法院|最高法院]]，试图撤销选举结果证明并使拜登的选票无效；这些挑战都被法院以缺乏证据或{{link-en|资格 (法律)|Standing (law)|资格}}为由驳回<ref name="trumpfraudclaims" />。

美国国会定于2021年1月6日召开会议，统计[[選舉人團_(美國)|選舉人團]]投票结果，特朗普宣布计划在会前举行集会，继续质疑多个州總統選舉结果的有效性。2020年12月18日，特朗普在社交媒體[[推特|推特]]發文宣布“1月6日在华盛顿举行大型抗议活动。记得来，（活动）将很疯狂！”{{refn|group=注| 原文：“Big protest in D.C. on January 6th. Be there, will be wild!”<ref name="bewild" />}}<ref name="bewild">{{Cite web|title=Nation's capital braces for violence as extremist groups converge to protest Trump's election loss|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2021/01/04/january-6-dc-protests-against-election-certification-could-violent/4132441001/|accessdate=2021-01-07|last=Carless|first=Will|work=USA TODAY|archivedate=2021-01-05|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105213603/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2021/01/04/january-6-dc-protests-against-election-certification-could-violent/4132441001/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":8">{{Cite web|date=2021-01-06|title='We're gonna kill Congress': Trump's far-right supporters promise violence at today's DC protests|url=https://www.rawstory.com/proud-boys-rally/|first=Jordan|last=Green|access-date=2021-01-09|work=[[The_Raw_Story|The Raw Story]]|archivedate=2021-01-08|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108052602/https://www.rawstory.com/proud-boys-rally/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

特朗普此前几天一直在暗示副总统[[邁克·彭斯|彭斯]]应该在國會認證全美各州選舉人票數時推翻拜登的胜選结果，但这并不在彭斯在[[美国宪法|美国宪法]]所授予的权力范围之内，而特朗普在1月6日正午发表的演讲中重复了这一呼吁。<ref name=":0" />同一天下午，彭斯发表了一封致国会的信，他在信中表示他并没有权力去接受或反对各州选举人团提供的选举结果。<ref name=":0" />

=== 事前策劃 ===
1月6日的「拯救美國遊行」（Save America March）由[[501(c)条款|501(c)(4)註冊非牟利組織]]「支持美國優先女士」（Women for America First）所策劃，此組織的主席{{link-en|艾米·克雷默|Amy Kremer}}是支持特朗普的[[茶黨運動|茶黨運動]]活躍分子。組織邀請支持者加入車隊前往首都華盛頓出席活動<ref name=cnbcjan9>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2021/01/09/pro-trump-dark-money-groups-organized-the-rally-that-led-to-deadly-capitol-hill-riot.html|title=Pro-Trump dark money groups organized the rally that led to deadly Capitol Hill riot|author=Schwartz, Brian|work=[[全國廣播公司商業頻道|全國廣播公司商業頻道]]|access-date=2021-01-09|date=2021-01-09|archivedate=2021-01-09|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109160237/https://www.cnbc.com/2021/01/09/pro-trump-dark-money-groups-organized-the-rally-that-led-to-deadly-capitol-hill-riot.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。特朗普在橢圓形草坪舉行的演講由Event Strategies籌辦，其創辦人Tim Unes有份協助特朗普2016年競選總統活動<ref name=cnbcjan9/>。

阿拉伯裔極右活躍人士{{link-en|阿里·亞歷山大|Ali Alexander}}被媒體揭發在1月6日前發表過支持衝擊國會言論，並且自稱與共和黨眾議員[[保羅·戈薩拉|保羅·戈薩拉]]、[[安迪·比格斯|安迪·比格斯]]和[[莫·布魯克斯|莫·布魯克斯]]一同策劃要「大幹一場」<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/opinion/op-ed/ej-montini/2021/01/10/reps-andy-biggs-paul-gosar-implicated-capitol-insurrection/6614177002/|title=Arizona Reps. Andy Biggs and Paul Gosar implicated by activist in Capitol insurrection|author=Montini, EJ|date=2021-01-10|access-date=2021-01-11|work={{le|亞利桑那共和報|The Arizona Republic}}|archivedate=2021-01-15|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115172719/https://www.azcentral.com/story/opinion/op-ed/ej-montini/2021/01/10/reps-andy-biggs-paul-gosar-implicated-capitol-insurrection/6614177002/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、「1月6日的事件就是我們四人主推的」<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Grim|first1=Ryan|last2=Chávez|first2=Aída|date=2021-01-11|title=Freedom Caucus Chair Andy Biggs Helped Plan January 6 Event, Lead Organizer Says|url=https://theintercept.com/2021/01/11/capitol-plot-andy-biggs-paul-gosar/|access-date=2021-01-12|work=The Intercept|archivedate=2021-01-11|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111234259/https://theintercept.com/2021/01/11/capitol-plot-andy-biggs-paul-gosar/|dead-url=no}}</ref>和「向還猶豫未決的國會議員施壓讓他們覺得『我不能站在那群示威者的對立方』。」比格斯在衝擊國會事件後否認與亞歷山大有任何聯繫<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Kuznia|first1=Rob|last2=Devine|first2=Curt|last3=Bronstein|first3=Scott|last4=Ortega|first4=Bob|date=2021-01-09|title=Extremists intensify calls for violence ahead of Inauguration Day|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/08/us/online-extremism-inauguration-capitol-invs/index.html|work=有線電視新聞網|accessdate=2021-01-16|archivedate=2021-01-11|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111171231/https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/08/us/online-extremism-inauguration-capitol-invs/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/stop-the-steal-organizer-in-hiding-after-denying-blame-for-riot|title='Stop the Steal' Organizer in Hiding After Denying Blame for Riot|first=Will|last=Sommer|date=2021-01-11|via=www.thedailybeast.com|accessdate=2021-01-16|archivedate=2021-01-11|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111045255/https://www.thedailybeast.com/stop-the-steal-organizer-in-hiding-after-denying-blame-for-riot|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last1=Anglen|first1=Robert|last2=Hansen|first2=Ronald J.|date=2021-01-10|title=Reps. Paul Gosar, Andy Biggs credited in video with organizing Trump crowd in DC on day of riot|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/news/politics/arizona/2021/01/10/paul-gosar-andy-biggs-credited-video-organizing-trump-crowd-dc/6603721002/|work=The Arizona Republic|accessdate=2021-01-16|archivedate=2021-01-15|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115172719/https://www.azcentral.com/story/news/politics/arizona/2021/01/10/paul-gosar-andy-biggs-credited-video-organizing-trump-crowd-dc/6603721002/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。而《華盛頓郵報》則報導有影片和社交發文顯示三名眾議員與亞歷山大早有交流<ref>{{Cite web|title=GOP Reps. Deny Giving 'Reconnaissance Tours' to Capitol Rioters|url=https://news.yahoo.com/gop-reps-deny-giving-reconnaissance-160235263.html|access-date=2021-01-14|work=news.yahoo.com|language=en-US|archivedate=2021-01-14|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114162012/https://news.yahoo.com/gop-reps-deny-giving-reconnaissance-160235263.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

衝擊國會的人在1月6日前數週就公開策劃妨礙國會認證總統選舉結果，包括對國會議員、彭斯和執法人員使用暴力<ref name=graff/>。他們選擇了主流網站如[[Reddit|Reddit]]和[[Twitter|推特]]以外的[[另類科技|另類科技]]社交平台如[[Parler|Parler]]、[[Telegram|Telegram]]或[[Gab|Gab]]等以避免其激進發文或媒體遭審查或刪除<ref name=Lytvyenko210106>{{Cite web|last1=Lytvyenko|first1=Jane|last2=Hensley-Clancy|first2=Molly|date=2021-01-06|title=The Rioters Who Took Over The Capitol Have Been Planning Online In The Open For Weeks|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/janelytvynenko/trump-rioters-planned-online|access-date=2021-01-08|work=BuzzFeed News|archivedate=2021-01-06|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106235519/https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/janelytvynenko/trump-rioters-planned-online|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=frenkeljan6>{{Cite news|last=Frenkel|first=Sheera|date=2021-01-06|title=The storming of Capitol Hill was organized on social media|work=紐約時報|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/06/us/politics/protesters-storm-capitol-hill-building.html|access-date=2021-01-06|archivedate=2021-01-06|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106220539/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/06/us/politics/protesters-storm-capitol-hill-building.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。這些平台上有不少人討論過實行騷亂的策略的話題，例如如何在街上躲過執法人員、需要利用什麼工具撬開門鎖、如何偷運武器進入首都華盛頓<ref name=frenkeljan6/>、教唆假扮成對立的[[安提法|安提法]]成員<ref name="auto41"/>、甚至是襲擊執法人員等<ref name=":8" />。

[[驕傲男孩|驕傲男孩]]和其他極右組織原本支持執法人員，但自[[2020－2021年美國選舉抗議活動|2020年12月12日抗議選舉結果示威]]起就開始對執法人員越發不配合<ref name=":8" />。其中「停止偷竊（選舉）」（Stop the Steal）團體於12月23日就在網上計劃過要佔領國會，並揚言與執法人員發生衝突時會故意讓事態升溫<ref>{{Cite web|last=McEvoy|first=Jemima|date=2021-01-07|title=Capitol Attack Was Planned Openly Online For Weeks – Police Still Weren't Ready|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jemimamcevoy/2021/01/07/capitol-attack-was-planned-openly-online-for-weeks-police-still-werent-ready/|access-date=2021-01-08|work=Forbes|archivedate=2021-01-11|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111045903/https://www.forbes.com/sites/jemimamcevoy/2021/01/07/capitol-attack-was-planned-openly-online-for-weeks-police-still-werent-ready/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。這些討論中不少都使用了語氣強烈的措辭如「戰爭」（war）和驚悚的畫像如以{{link-en|絞索|noose}}吊起他們提議肅清的政客的自制動畫<ref name=Lytvyenko210106/>。

==== 資金來源 ====

資助「支持美國優先女士」運作的「{{link-en|美國優先政策|America First Policies}}」團體的主席是曾經獲得特朗普提名出任小型企業管理署署長的[[琳達·麥馬漢|琳達·麥馬漢]]，它被媒體形容為支持特朗普的{{link-en|黑金政治|dark money}}團體（因為註冊為非牟利組織而無需披露資金來源）<ref name=cnbcjan9/>。陰謀論者[[亚历克斯·琼斯|亚历克斯·琼斯]]表示，他捐出了50萬美元用以予約[[椭圆形草坪|椭圆形草坪]]以舉行1月6日的拯救美國演講會，甚至[[白宮|白宮]]有人請求他率領特朗普支持者遊行至國會<ref name="AlexJonesClaim">{{cite news|first=Graig|last=Graziosi|title=Alex Jones says he paid $500,000 for rally that led to Capitol riot|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-election-2020/alex-jones-paid-rally-capitol-riot-b1784603.html|date=2021-01-08|work=[[獨立報|獨立報]]|accessdate=2021-01-17|archivedate=2021-01-14|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114161541/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-election-2020/alex-jones-paid-rally-capitol-riot-b1784603.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。「{{link-en|美國轉捩點|Turning Point USA}}」團體的創辦人{{link-en|查理·柯克|Charlie Kirk (activist)}}在推特稱他安排了超過80輛大巴到達首都國會<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.com/charlie-kirk-insurrection-buses-washington-tweet-1560727|first=Ewan|last=Palmer|title=Charlie Kirk Says Not Everyone in Capitol Mob Was an Insurrectionist|date=2021-01-12|work=[[新聞周刊|新聞周刊]]|accessdate=2021-01-17|archivedate=2021-01-12|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112150142/https://www.newsweek.com/charlie-kirk-insurrection-buses-washington-tweet-1560727|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其他個別人士透過網上眾籌平台[[GoFundMe|GoFundMe]]欲募款獲得前往首都參與示威活動的資金<ref name="NYTrioteranalysis">{{Cite news|last1=Barry|first1=Dan|last2=McIntire|first2=Mike|last3=Rosenberg|first3=Matthew|date=2021-01-09|title='Our President Wants Us Here': The Mob That Stormed the Capitol|work=紐約時報|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/09/us/capitol-rioters.html|access-date=2021-01-10|archivedate=2021-01-09|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109232819/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/09/us/capitol-rioters.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，GoFundMe自騷亂發生起就中止了這類眾籌項目，但有一部分項目在被中止前已經成功募得目標金額<ref>{{Cite web|last=Wong|first=Venessa|date=2021-01-08|title=Trump Supporters Used GoFundMe To "Build An Army" In DC|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/venessawong/trump-gofundme-dc-january-6|access-date=2021-01-10|work=BuzzFeed News|archivedate=2021-01-09|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109235458/https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/venessawong/trump-gofundme-dc-january-6|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 執法部隊先前部署 ===
[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿哥伦比亚特区]][[國家廣場|國家廣場]]一帶日常治安由幾個不同機關分擔管理不同區域。[[白宮|白宮]]一帶由隸屬於[[美國國土安全部|國土安全部]]的[[美国特勤局|特勤局]]管轄；特朗普進行演講的[[橢圓形草坪|橢圓形草坪]]屬於聯邦機關[[美國公園警察|公園警察]]管轄範圍；隸屬於特區市政府的{{link-en|哥倫比亞特區市警察局|Metropolitan Police Department of the District of Columbia}}負責國家廣場內的所有公共街道；屬於聯邦機關的[[美國國會警察|國會警察]]負責[[國會山莊|國會山莊]]一帶公園及其建築群的保安，本身隸屬於由[[眾議院警衛官|眾議院警衛官]]、{{link-en|美國參議院警衛官|Sergeant at Arms of the United States Senate|參議院警衛官}}和{{link-en|國會建築師|Architect of the Capitol}}組成的{{link-en|國會警察委員會|Capitol Police Board}}。

华盛顿特区市长[[穆里尔·鲍泽|穆里尔·鲍泽]]在2020年12月31日要求在预期的示威活动中部署哥伦比亚特区[[美國國民警衛隊|國民警衛隊]]，以支援当地警方。她在请求中写道，这些人员不会携带武器，他们将主要负责[[人群管理|人群管理]]和指挥交通，让警方专注于保安工作。代理国防部长[[克里斯托弗·米勒|克里斯托弗·米勒]]于2021年1月4日批准了这一请求。批准部署340名士兵，但任何时候不会同时部署超过114人<ref>{{Cite web|title=Pentagon approves DC mayor's request to deploy National Guard for upcoming demonstrations|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/04/politics/muriel-bowser-dc-national-guard-protests/index.html|authors=Alex Marquardt, Barbara Starr, Alison Main and Devan Cole|access-date=2021-01-06|work=有線電視新聞網|archivedate=2021-01-06|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106212843/https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/04/politics/muriel-bowser-dc-national-guard-protests/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。騷亂發生前一天，鮑澤在一封給[[美国司法部|司法部]]的公開信中指，特區政府不會在未與市警察局商討前擅自請求其他聯邦執法機關的支援<ref name="MyreWhereWere2021">{{cite news |last1=Myre |first1=Greg |title=Where Was Security When A Pro-Trump Mob Stormed The Capitol? |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/congress-electoral-college-tally-live-updates/2021/01/07/954349992/where-was-the-security-when-a-mob-stormed-the-capitol |access-date=2021-01-12 |work=[[全國公共廣播電台|全國公共廣播電台]] |date=2021-01-07 |archivedate=2021-01-10 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210110113309/https://www.npr.org/sections/congress-electoral-college-tally-live-updates/2021/01/07/954349992/where-was-the-security-when-a-mob-stormed-the-capitol |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

騷亂發生前三天，[[美國國防部|國防部]]曾經兩度提議派駐國民警衛隊到國會，但都被國會警察以不必要為由回絕<ref name=longjan7>{{cite news |title=Capitol Police rejected offers of federal help to quell mob |url=https://apnews.com/article/capitol-police-reject-federal-help-9c39a4ddef0ab60a48828a07e4d03380 |date=2021-01-07 |work=[[美聯社|美聯社]] |first1=Colleen |last1=Long |first2=Lolita |last2=Baldor |first3=Michael |last3=Balsamo |first4=Nomaan |last4=Merchant |accessdate=2021-01-17 |archivedate=2021-01-13 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210113193518/https://apnews.com/article/capitol-police-reject-federal-help-9c39a4ddef0ab60a48828a07e4d03380 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，儘管這時候國會警察的情報部已經收到一份12頁紙的報告書指1月6日國會一帶會爆發騷亂，但報告書在警察局內似乎沒有獲得廣泛傳閱<ref>{{cite web |last1=Leonnig |first1=Carol |title=Capitol Police intelligence report warned three days before attack that 'Congress itself' could be targeted |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/capitol-police-intelligence-warning/2021/01/15/c8b50744-5742-11eb-a08b-f1381ef3d207_story.html |work=華盛頓郵報 |access-date=2021-01-16 |date=2021-01-15 |archivedate=2021-01-16 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116004540/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/capitol-police-intelligence-warning/2021/01/15/c8b50744-5742-11eb-a08b-f1381ef3d207_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。特區市警察局代理局長{{link-en|羅伯特·康提|Robert Contee}}於騷亂後表示市警察局並沒有收到過國會大廈有被暴徒衝擊闖入風險的情報<ref name="politico-bertrand-2021">{{cite web |last1=Bertrand |first1=Natasha |title=Justice Department warns of national security fallout from Capitol Hill insurrection |url=https://www.politico.com/news/2021/01/07/capitol-hill-riots-doj-456178 |work=[[Politico|Politico]] |access-date=2021-01-08 |date=2021-01-07 |archivedate=2021-01-13 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210113193532/https://www.politico.com/news/2021/01/07/capitol-hill-riots-doj-456178 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。已經引咎辭職的國會警察局局長{{link-en|史提芬·桑德|Steven Sund}}事後則表示制定了處理「[[美利堅合眾國憲法第一條修正案|第一修正案]]（言論與集會等自由）活動」的對策，但並沒有想像到示威會演變為暴力佔領國會大廈的局面，因此1月6日派遣現場的國會警察以一般制服執勤，而非以防暴裝備上陣<ref name=nakedpolice>{{Cite web |title=Capitol police were overrun, 'left naked' against rioters |url=https://apnews.com/article/politics-police-riots-michael-pence-capitol-siege-c3a5973a68c699ff6a57cdd76d675e29 |first1=Colleen |last1=Long |first2=Michael |last2=Balsamo |first3=Lisa |last3=Mascaro |work=[[美聯社|美聯社]] |access-date=2021-01-11 |date=2021-01-10 |archivedate=2021-01-10 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210110235835/https://apnews.com/article/politics-police-riots-michael-pence-capitol-siege-c3a5973a68c699ff6a57cdd76d675e29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[美国陆军部长|陸軍部長]]{{link-en|瑞安·麥卡錫|Ryan D. McCarthy}}表示各執法機關最初預計1月6日在國會示威的人數在二千至八萬人的範圍內<ref name=longjan7/>，[[美國國家公園管理局|國家公園管理局]]於1月5日按當日已經聚集的人群評估翌日「拯救美國遊行」的規模約為三萬人<ref>{{Cite web|last=Shabad|first=Rebecca|date=2021-01-06|title=Trump to address D.C. rally where as many as 30,000 people are expected|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/blog/electoral-college-certification-updates-n1252864|access-date=2021-01-11|work=NBC News|archivedate=2021-01-10|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210110083001/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/blog/electoral-college-certification-updates-n1252864|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

評論認為這系列消極的警力部署是受到[[乔治·弗洛伊德之死引发的示威活动|乔治·弗洛伊德之死引发的示威活动]]爆發時，各地防暴警察過度執法所引起的爭議的影響，這個判斷在國會騷亂爆發後演變成左派對[[#有關選擇性執法的指控|警方過度寬鬆處理右派示威者]]的指控<ref name="MyreWhereWere2021"/>。

