之后，国会大厦内发生枪击事件，众议院议事厅前门发生武装对峙。<ref name=":22">{{Cite web|title=HAPPENING NOW: Armed standoff inside US Capitol, shots fired|url=https://wqow.com/2021/01/06/happening-now-armed-standoff-inside-us-capitol-shots-fired/|date=2021-01-06|last=Berge|first=Clint|language=en-US|access-date=2021-01-06|work=[[WQOW|WQOW]]|archivedate=2021-01-06|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106212531/https://wqow.com/2021/01/06/happening-now-armed-standoff-inside-us-capitol-shots-fired/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":32">{{Cite web|title=Updates: Capitol breached by protesters, shots reported fired inside|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/capitol-breached-protesters/story?id=75081629|author=<!-- Staff writer(s) -->|language=en|access-date=2021-01-06|work=[[ABC新聞|ABC新聞]]|archivedate=2021-01-06|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106212039/https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/capitol-breached-protesters/story?id=75081629|dead-url=no}}</ref>支持特朗普的暴力示威者闯入国会大厦后，多名警察在众议院议事厅内拔枪，并将枪口对准用家具挡住的议事厅大门。<ref>{{Cite news|date=2021-01-06|title=Police draw guns inside the Capitol.|language=en-US|work=紐約時報|url=https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/01/06/us/washington-dc-protests/police-draw-guns-inside-the-capitol|access-date=2021-01-06|issn=0362-4331|archivedate=2021-01-06|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106222936/https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/01/06/us/washington-dc-protests/police-draw-guns-inside-the-capitol|dead-url=no}}</ref>一名闯入者在国会大厦内被执法人员开枪击中胸部（亦有說法是被開槍擊中頸部<ref>{{Cite news|date=2021-01-07|title=國會動亂遭擊斃女子身分曝光 傳曾效力美國空軍[影]|work=[[中央通訊社|中央通訊社]]|url=https://www.cna.com.tw/news/aopl/202101070252.aspx|access-date=2021-01-08|archivedate=2021-01-10|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210110003352/https://www.cna.com.tw/news/aopl/202101070252.aspx|dead-url=no|language=zh-tw}}</ref>），随后伤重不治。<ref name="wapojan6" />一名执法官员告诉《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》，警方认为死者没有携带武器，但开出致命一枪的警员在开枪时并不知道这一点，而警方了解到许多闯入者都秘密持有武器。<ref name="wapojan6" />闯入国会大厦的暴力示威者还冲进众议院议长[[南希·佩洛西|南希·佩洛西]]的办公室，掀翻桌子并撕毁了挂在墙壁上的照片。有蒙面人带着警用塑料手铐企图活捉佩洛西和副总统[[迈克·彭斯|彭斯]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Goldman |first1=Adam |last2=Benner |first2=Katie |title=The F.B.I. arrests two men who had carried plastic restraints into the Capitol. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/10/us/politics/capitol-zip-ties-arrest.html |work=紐約時報 |date=2021-01-10 |accessdate=2021-01-13 |archivedate=2021-01-11 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111183315/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/10/us/politics/capitol-zip-ties-arrest.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>；西佛吉尼亚州众议员{{Internal link helper/en|德里克·埃文斯|Derrick Evans (politician)}}直播自己冲击国会，并在被捕后辞职<ref>{{cite web |last1=Astor |first1=Maggie |title=Derrick Evans, a West Virginia legislator who stormed the Capitol, has resigned. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/09/us/politics/derrick-evans-resigns-capitol-riot.html |work=紐約時報 |date=2021-01-09 |accessdate=2021-01-13 |archivedate=2021-01-09 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109222034/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/09/us/politics/derrick-evans-resigns-capitol-riot.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。同时国会大厦内也发生了[[抢劫|抢劫]]事件，有示威者搬走了[[美國眾議院議長|众议院议长]]的讲台，并将其發布在[[eBay|eBay]]上拍卖。<ref>{{Cite web|title=美抗议者搬走众议院议长讲台后，eBay上出现疑似拍卖照片|url=https://3w.huanqiu.com/a/c36dc8/41Py2FFdJMm|accessdate=|author=张晓雅|date=2021-01-07|format=|work=[[环球网|环球网]]|language=中文|archivedate=2021-01-09|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109011730/https://3w.huanqiu.com/a/c36dc8/41Py2FFdJMm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Benner|first1=Katie|last2=Haberman|first2=Maggie|last3=Schmidt|first3=Michael S.|date=2021-01-06|title=Live Updates: Pro-Trump Mob Breaches Capitol, Halting Vote Certification|language=en-US|work=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/01/06/us/washington-dc-protests|access-date=2021-01-06|issn=0362-4331|archivedate=2021-01-06|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106202204/https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/01/06/us/washington-dc-protests|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Marauding protesters vandalize Speaker Pelosi's office.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/06/us/politics/marauding-protesters-vandalize-speaker-pelosis-office.html|date=2021-01-06|work=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]|first1=Erin|last1=Schaff|first2=Sabrina|last2=Tavernise|access-date=2021-01-06|archivedate=2021-01-06|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106210311/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/06/us/politics/marauding-protesters-vandalize-speaker-pelosis-office.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=2021-01-07|title=示威者闖國會偷眾院議長講台　疑在eBay出售|newspaper=東方日報|url=https://hk.on.cc/hk/bkn/cnt/intnews/20210107/bkn-20210107161233448-0107_00992_001.html?view=d|access-date=2021-01-09|archivedate=2021-01-14|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114195850/https://hk.on.cc/hk/bkn/cnt/intnews/20210107/bkn-20210107161233448-0107_00992_001.html?view=d|dead-url=no}}</ref>国会警察报告说，大楼已被“捣毁”。<ref name="WilsonGrenadesDeployed" />观察者看到大楼里所有的位置都有“碎片、垃圾，都在电梯里，东西被撞倒，柱子也被撞倒”。<ref>{{cite web|first=Adrienne|last=Vogt|url=https://www.cnn.com/politics/live-news/congress-electoral-college-vote-count-2021/index.html|title=CNN reporter describes debris and smell of tear gas inside Capitol while being evacuated|work=有線電視新聞|date=2021-01-06|accessdate=2021-01-07|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106201229/https://www.cnn.com/politics/live-news/congress-electoral-college-vote-count-2021/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>国家雕像大厅的玻璃窗被打破。一些暴动者在国会大厦外攻击了在现场报道的记者<ref name=cmgstatement>{{cite news |title=CMG calls on U.S. to protect reporters in Capitol Hill |url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2021-01-07/CMG-calls-on-U-S-to-protect-reporters-in-Capitol-Hill-WQWBjV19jq/index.html |accessdate=2021-01-07 |work=[[中國環球電視網|中國環球電視網]] |date=2021-01-07 |language=en |archivedate=2021-01-07 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107103142/https://news.cgtn.com/news/2021-01-07/CMG-calls-on-U-S-to-protect-reporters-in-Capitol-Hill-WQWBjV19jq/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，还砸毁了[[美联社|美联社]]的摄录设备。<ref>{{cite web|title=Mob swarms media outside Capitol, damages equipment|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/video/mob-swarms-media-outside-capitol-damages-equipment-98983493908|work=[[NBC新聞|NBC新聞]]|access-date=2021-01-07|archivedate=2021-01-07|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107015509/https://www.nbcnews.com/video/mob-swarms-media-outside-capitol-damages-equipment-98983493908|dead-url=no}}</ref>在国会大厦的暴力事件中，有多名警员受伤。<ref name="MultipleInjuries" />两名国会警察因为涉嫌充当暴徒内应、为其开道引路，而被停职调查<ref>{{cite web |title=Several US Capitol Police officers have been suspended after welcoming pro-Trump rioters into the building. 10 to 15 officers under investigation, lawmaker says. |url=http://currently.att.yahoo.com/att/cm/2-us-capitol-police-officers-230623925.html |work=[[雅虎|雅虎]]新聞 |accessdate=2021-01-13 |archivedate=2021-01-12 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112004256/https://currently.att.yahoo.com/att/cm/2-us-capitol-police-officers-230623925.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

