r.illinois.edu/coup-detat-project-cdp/statement_jan.27.2021|title=It Was an Attempted Coup: The Cline Center's Coup D'état Project Categorizes the January 6, 2021 Assault on the US Capitol|publisher=Cline Center for Advanced Social Research|access-date=2021-03-28|archive-date=2021-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210204105008/https://clinecenter.illinois.edu/coup-detat-project-cdp/statement_jan.27.2021|dead-url=no}}</ref>。一些政治学者将冲击事件归类为[[自我政变|自我政变]]，即[[政府首脑|政府首脑]]试图胁迫政府其他部门以巩固权力<ref name="UiQHf">{{cite web|last=Ingraham|first=Christopher|title=How experts define the deadly mob attack at the U.S. Capitol|date=2021-01-13|access-date=2021-01-31|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/2021/01/13/autogolpe-self-coup-capitol/|website=The Washington Post|archive-date=2021-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127080308/https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/2021/01/13/autogolpe-self-coup-capitol/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。特朗普在任时的[[美国国家安全会议|国家安全委员会]]的成员，学者{{tsl|en|Fiona Hill (presidential advisor)|菲奥娜·希尔 (总统顾问)|菲奥娜·希尔}}将冲击事件及之前几个月特朗普有关这一事件的行为描述为试图进行自我政变<ref name="IDgK3">{{cite web|last=Hill|first=Fiona|title=Yes, It Was a Coup Attempt. Here's Why.|date=2021-01-11|access-date=2021-01-31|url=https://www.politico.com/news/magazine/2021/01/11/capitol-riot-self-coup-trump-fiona-hill-457549|website=Politico|archive-date=2021-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201225033/https://www.politico.com/news/magazine/2021/01/11/capitol-riot-self-coup-trump-fiona-hill-457549|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

